{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "web:second-samuel.22",
    "translationId": "web",
    "bookSlug": "second-samuel",
    "chapterNumber": 22,
    "referenceLabel": "2 Samuel 22",
    "summary": "Source text for 2 Samuel 22 in World English Bible."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "web:second-samuel.22.1",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "second-samuel",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Samuel 22:1",
      "text": "David spoke to Yahweh the words of this song in the day that Yahweh delivered him out of the hand of all his enemies, and out of the hand of Saul,",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "web:second-samuel.22.2",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "second-samuel",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Samuel 22:2",
      "text": "and he said: “Yahweh is my rock, my fortress, and my deliverer, even mine;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:second-samuel.22.3",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "second-samuel",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Samuel 22:3",
      "text": "God is my rock in whom I take refuge; my shield, and the horn of my salvation, my high tower, and my refuge. My savior, you save me from violence.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:second-samuel.22.4",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "second-samuel",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Samuel 22:4",
      "text": "I call on Yahweh, who is worthy to be praised; So shall I be saved from my enemies.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:second-samuel.22.5",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "second-samuel",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Samuel 22:5",
      "text": "For the waves of death surrounded me. The floods of ungodliness made me afraid.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:second-samuel.22.6",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "second-samuel",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Samuel 22:6",
      "text": "The cords of Sheol were around me. The snares of death caught me.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:second-samuel.22.7",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "second-samuel",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Samuel 22:7",
      "text": "In my distress, I called on Yahweh. Yes, I called to my God. He heard my voice out of his temple. My cry came into his ears.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:second-samuel.22.8",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "second-samuel",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Samuel 22:8",
      "text": "Then the earth shook and trembled. The foundations of heaven quaked and were shaken, because he was angry.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:second-samuel.22.9",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "second-samuel",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Samuel 22:9",
      "text": "Smoke went up out of his nostrils. Consuming fire came out of his mouth. Coals were kindled by it.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:second-samuel.22.10",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "second-samuel",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Samuel 22:10",
      "text": "He bowed the heavens also, and came down. Thick darkness was under his feet.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:second-samuel.22.11",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "second-samuel",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Samuel 22:11",
      "text": "He rode on a cherub, and flew. Yes, he was seen on the wings of the wind.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:second-samuel.22.12",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "second-samuel",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Samuel 22:12",
      "text": "He made darkness a shelter around himself, gathering of waters, and thick clouds of the skies.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:second-samuel.22.13",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "second-samuel",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Samuel 22:13",
      "text": "At the brightness before him, coals of fire were kindled.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:second-samuel.22.14",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "second-samuel",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Samuel 22:14",
      "text": "Yahweh thundered from heaven. The Most High uttered his voice.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:second-samuel.22.15",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "second-samuel",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Samuel 22:15",
      "text": "He sent out arrows and scattered them, lightning and confused them.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:second-samuel.22.16",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "second-samuel",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Samuel 22:16",
      "text": "Then the channels of the sea appeared. The foundations of the world were laid bare by Yahweh’s rebuke, at the blast of the breath of his nostrils.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:second-samuel.22.17",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "second-samuel",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Samuel 22:17",
      "text": "He sent from on high and he took me. He drew me out of many waters.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:second-samuel.22.18",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "second-samuel",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Samuel 22:18",
      "text": "He delivered me from my strong enemy, from those who hated me, for they were too mighty for me.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:second-samuel.22.19",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "second-samuel",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Samuel 22:19",
      "text": "They came on me in the day of my calamity, but Yahweh was my support.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:second-samuel.22.20",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "second-samuel",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Samuel 22:20",
      "text": "He also brought me out into a large place. He delivered me, because he delighted in me.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:second-samuel.22.21",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "second-samuel",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Samuel 22:21",
      "text": "Yahweh rewarded me according to my righteousness. He rewarded me according to the cleanness of my hands.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:second-samuel.22.22",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "second-samuel",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Samuel 22:22",
      "text": "For I have kept Yahweh’s ways, and have not wickedly departed from my God.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:second-samuel.22.23",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "second-samuel",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Samuel 22:23",
      "text": "For all his ordinances were before me. As for his statutes, I didn’t depart from them.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:second-samuel.22.24",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "second-samuel",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Samuel 22:24",
      "text": "I was also perfect toward him. I kept myself from my iniquity.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:second-samuel.22.25",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "second-samuel",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Samuel 22:25",
      "text": "Therefore Yahweh has rewarded me according to my righteousness, According to my cleanness in his eyesight.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:second-samuel.22.26",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "second-samuel",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Samuel 22:26",
      "text": "With the merciful you will show yourself merciful. With the perfect man you will show yourself perfect.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:second-samuel.22.27",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "second-samuel",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 27,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Samuel 22:27",
      "text": "With the pure you will show yourself pure. With the crooked you will show yourself shrewd.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:second-samuel.22.28",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "second-samuel",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 28,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Samuel 22:28",
      "text": "You will save the afflicted people, but your eyes are on the arrogant, that you may bring them down.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:second-samuel.22.29",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "second-samuel",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 29,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Samuel 22:29",
      "text": "For you are my lamp, Yahweh. Yahweh will light up my darkness.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:second-samuel.22.30",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "second-samuel",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 30,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Samuel 22:30",
      "text": "For by you, I run against a troop. By my God, I leap over a wall.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:second-samuel.22.31",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "second-samuel",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 31,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Samuel 22:31",
      "text": "As for God, his way is perfect. Yahweh’s word is tested. He is a shield to all those who take refuge in him.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:second-samuel.22.32",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "second-samuel",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 32,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Samuel 22:32",
      "text": "For who is God, besides Yahweh? Who is a rock, besides our God?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:second-samuel.22.33",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "second-samuel",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 33,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Samuel 22:33",
      "text": "God is my strong fortress. He makes my way perfect.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:second-samuel.22.34",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "second-samuel",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 34,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Samuel 22:34",
      "text": "He makes his feet like hinds’ feet, and sets me on my high places.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:second-samuel.22.35",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "second-samuel",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 35,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Samuel 22:35",
      "text": "He teaches my hands to war, so that my arms bend a bow of bronze.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:second-samuel.22.36",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "second-samuel",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 36,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Samuel 22:36",
      "text": "You have also given me the shield of your salvation. Your gentleness has made me great.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:second-samuel.22.37",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "second-samuel",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 37,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Samuel 22:37",
      "text": "You have enlarged my steps under me. My feet have not slipped.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:second-samuel.22.38",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "second-samuel",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 38,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Samuel 22:38",
      "text": "I have pursued my enemies and destroyed them. I didn’t turn again until they were consumed.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:second-samuel.22.39",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "second-samuel",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 39,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Samuel 22:39",
      "text": "I have consumed them, and struck them through, so that they can’t arise. Yes, they have fallen under my feet.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:second-samuel.22.40",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "second-samuel",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 40,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Samuel 22:40",
      "text": "For you have armed me with strength for the battle. You have subdued under me those who rose up against me.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:second-samuel.22.41",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "second-samuel",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 41,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Samuel 22:41",
      "text": "You have also made my enemies turn their backs to me, that I might cut off those who hate me.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:second-samuel.22.42",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "second-samuel",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 42,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Samuel 22:42",
      "text": "They looked, but there was no one to save; even to Yahweh, but he didn’t answer them.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:second-samuel.22.43",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "second-samuel",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 43,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Samuel 22:43",
      "text": "Then I beat them as small as the dust of the earth. I crushed them as the mire of the streets, and spread them abroad.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:second-samuel.22.44",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "second-samuel",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 44,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Samuel 22:44",
      "text": "You also have delivered me from the strivings of my people. You have kept me to be the head of the nations. A people whom I have not known will serve me.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:second-samuel.22.45",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "second-samuel",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 45,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Samuel 22:45",
      "text": "The foreigners will submit themselves to me. As soon as they hear of me, they will obey me.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:second-samuel.22.46",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "second-samuel",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 46,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Samuel 22:46",
      "text": "The foreigners will fade away, and will come trembling out of their close places.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:second-samuel.22.47",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "second-samuel",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 47,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Samuel 22:47",
      "text": "Yahweh lives! Blessed be my rock! Exalted be God, the rock of my salvation,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:second-samuel.22.48",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "second-samuel",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 48,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Samuel 22:48",
      "text": "even the God who executes vengeance for me, who brings down peoples under me,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:second-samuel.22.49",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "second-samuel",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 49,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Samuel 22:49",
      "text": "who brings me away from my enemies. Yes, you lift me up above those who rise up against me. You deliver me from the violent man.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:second-samuel.22.50",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "second-samuel",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 50,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Samuel 22:50",
      "text": "Therefore I will give thanks to you, Yahweh, among the nations, and will sing praises to your name.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:second-samuel.22.51",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "second-samuel",
      "chapterNumber": 22,
      "verseNumber": 51,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Samuel 22:51",
      "text": "He gives great deliverance to his king, and shows loving kindness to his anointed, to David and to his offspring, forever more.”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
